Here is a function in Java that can be used to find the factorial of a given number:

```java
public class Factorial{

    public static long factorial(int n){
        long result = 1;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
            result = result * i;
        }

        return result;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println(factorial(5)); //output should be 120 
    }
}
```

This function takes an integer as an argument and returns its factorial as a long value. It calculates the result by multiplying all positive integers less than or equal to the input integer. You can test it by calling it in the main method, as shown in the example above.

